reviews.text:
Good and simple Japanese food.
Omakase is amazing, you need to book one day before but it worth trying!
Fushion JPN cuisine with sincere hospitality. Foods are exceedingly fresh and present with heart. Yet, it is assumed to be a bit overpriced, and await for more improvement to deserve it.
Very good
One of the "feels like home" service that you can find in HK, which is rare by the way. The people and their food is really nice! Try getting their fatty salmon and their egg roll with cheese.
Quite creative dishes and you can manage your own budget
